    <part>
        <title>Introduction to SOLOR</title>
        <partintro>
            <para>Prior to discussion of the System Of Logically Oriented Representation (SOLOR),
                the Department of Veterans Affairs's ISAAC (InformaticS Architecture Acceleration)
                must be referenced. ISAAC is an architecture framework that strives for a holistic
                approach to support an integrated delivery of iterative revisions of specifications,
                services, and content. ISAAC's design philosophy calls for an approach that supports
                novelty within a rigorous—and vertically integrated—deployment pipeline that is
                based on existing software development best practices. Moreover, it embraces DevOps
                culture and practice by emphasizing collaboration and communication while automating
                the process of product delivery. The vision for development within the ISAAC
                framework is one that enables knowledge engineers, developers, testers, build
                managers, and operations personnel to work together effectively to deliver assets to
                the points of care and analysis. </para>
            <para>Within the ISAAC architecture, KOMET (KnOwledge Management EnvironmenT) defines a
                modular system and a service platform for clinical knowledge management that
                implements a complete and dynamic component model. KOMET provides an environment for
                the modularization of knowledge resources into bundles. Each bundle is a tightly
                coupled, dynamically loadable collection of terminology, terminological knowledge
                assertions, A-Box assertions regarding rules, transformation, and files that
                explicitly declare their external dependencies—if any. To support the content within
                the ISAAC architecture, SOLOR's main goal is to provide an open-source terminology
                architecture that cultivates the relationships between terminologies and allows
                knowledge to be shared in one consumable format. Moreover, it strives to remove the
                complexities of various content, which are currently delivered by isolated silo
                organizations who place the implementation burden upon their consumers.</para>
        </partintro>
